You can use logstash to reindex the data with some filters. For filtering the date field you can use the date filter plugin.

Below is the format

        date {
           match =&gt; [ sourcefield , &lt;date-format&gt; ]
           target =&gt; destinationfield
        }

you can find the documentation [here][1]

Sample conf file

    input {
        elasticsearch {
            hosts =&gt; &quot;host
            index =&gt; &quot;index&quot;
            query =&gt; &#39;{ &quot;query&quot;: { &quot;match_all&quot;: {} } }&#39;
            scroll =&gt; &quot;20m&quot;
            docinfo =&gt; true
        }
    }
    filter {
        date {
               match =&gt; [ sourcefield , &lt;date-format&gt; ]
               target =&gt; destinationfield
        }
    }
    output {
        elasticsearch {
            hosts =&gt; &quot;host&quot;
            index =&gt; &quot;new-index&quot;
    }


  [1]: https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/logstash/current/plugins-filters-date.html#plugins-filters-date-target

